The course will introduce main physical and chemical processes in atmosphere and whole climate system, their connections, mathematical apparatus for the description and measurement methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To give an overview of atmospheric physical and chemical processes with mathematic methods. To describe the connections and dynamics in climate system.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course the student  1) has an overview of main chemical reactions in atmosphere, its chemical composition and measurement methods; 2) has a quantified understanding of connections between the structure, composition and dynamics of the atmosphere using simplified equations; 3) is able to explain the global energy budget; 4) will explain the feedbacks and inner unstability mechanisms of climate system; 5) can discuss the climate change causes including anthropogenic causes.
